com.complexible.common.io
Interface PageManager

All Superinterfaces:
Flushable
public interface PageManager
extends Flushable

A PageManager is responsible for the management of a set of PagedFiles and their Pages.

Since:
0.3
Version:
0.3
Author:
Pedro Oliveira

getPage

Page getPage(long theID,
             boolean create)
             throws IOException
Get the Page with the given ID, creating it if necessary. If a new page is created, the contents of the new page is undefined so performing a Page.read() on the result might return arbitrary results.

freePage

void freePage(long theID)
Frees the page identified by the given ID which means the page manager can reuse that page for the next request to create a new page.

getPageSize

int getPageSize()
Get the maximum number of bytes a Page can have including the header, in bytes. WARNING: Note that this number includes any bytes that will be used for the header in the page so the amount of data that can be written to the page will be less than this value. The header size might vary for a page
